description: Two American troops and a civilian were killed in central Syria on Saturday after an alleged member of the Islamic State group opened fire on a joint US-Syrian patrol, officials said. Donald Trump promised retaliation.

headline: French farmers angered by government culling of diseased cows
description: After clashes at a farm in southern France and the culling of 208 cows, tensions are rising between some agricultural unions and the government, which has stuck to its contested disease prevention strategy.

headline: Sant Ambroeus brings Italian flair to Paris's Latin Quarter
description: The New York café-restaurant frequented by celebrities has opened a new location in the elegant Saint-Germain-des-Prés district, offering an Italian-American menu in an atmosphere inspired by the 1930s.

headline: 'La Cage aux Folles': Paris reclaims the flamboyant musical
description: French audiences mostly know 'La Cage aux Folles' from the film adaptation of Jean Poiret's play, featuring Michel Serrault's exuberant performance. But it is also a triumphant Broadway classic, freed from clichés about homosexuality. Now, director Olivier Py and actor Laurent Lafitte bring the musical to the Théâtre du Châtelet in Paris.

description: Le Monde takes a look back at the the signing of the Paris Agreement in the French capital on December 12, 2015, a major geopolitical agreement reached after two weeks of intense negotiations that aimed to limit global warming to 'well below' 2°C and at 'pursuing efforts' to keep the temperature increase to 1.5°C.

headline: The mysterious 'knocker' scaring elderly women in a Brittany town
description: For more than two years, a prowler has been knocking on doors and shutters during the night in a village in Brittany, France, creating a climate of fear among his preferred targets: elderly women. Authorities were slow to take the case seriously.

headline: How the Israeli army is razing the part of Gaza it is supposed to withdraw from
description: Despite the ceasefire that was declared on October 10, Israel has continued to raze many buildings east of the 'yellow line' in the Gaza Strip, according to local residents and satellite images of the enclave.
